---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "Final Grade Calculator | What Do I Need on My Final?",
  description: "Calculate exactly what score you need on your final exam to keep your A or pass the class. Stop guessing and start studying effectively.",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": []
    },
    {
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": meta.title,
      "description": meta.description,
      "datePublished": meta.published
    }
  ]
};
---
<SiteLayout site="siliconbased" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/final-calculator" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Final Grade Calculator</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Find out exactly what score you need on your final exam.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div class="error-message" id="error-msg"></div>

      <div class="input-grid">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="current-grade">Current Grade (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="current-grade" min="0" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 85">
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="target-grade">Target Grade (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="target-grade" min="0" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 90">
        </div>
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="final-weight">Final Exam Weight (%)</label>
          <input type="number" id="final-weight" min="0" max="100" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 20">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="result-card" id="results" style="display: none;">
        <div style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.1rem;">You need to score at least</div>
        <div class="result-value" id="res-score">0.00%</div>
        <div style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 0.5rem;" id="res-message">on your final to get a 90% in the class.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explainer">
      <h2>How to Use the Final Grade Calculator</h2>
      <p>The end of the semester can be incredibly stressful, especially when your final grade is hanging in the balance. Instead of guessing how hard you need to study, our <strong>final grade calculator</strong> provides the exact percentage you must achieve on your last exam to reach your goal.</p>

      <p>Whether you're trying to keep an A, secure a passing grade, or figure out if you can afford to skip studying entirely, this tool handles the math instantly. If you're dealing with geometry or math homework before your exam, you might also find our <a href="/triangle-calculator" style="color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: underline;">triangle calculator</a> helpful.</p>

      <h3>The Formula Behind the Calculation</h3>
      <p>Calculating the required grade on a final exam relies on a simple algebraic formula based on weighted averages. Here is how it works under the hood:</p>
      <div style="background: var(--bg-color); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; font-family: var(--font-mono); text-align: center; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
        Final Exam Score = (Target Grade - (Current Grade &times; (1 - Final Weight))) / Final Weight
      </div>
      <p>Let's break down the variables used in this equation:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Current Grade:</strong> Your overall grade in the class <em>before</em> taking the final exam. This should include all homework, quizzes, midterms, and participation points graded so far.</li>
        <li><strong>Target Grade:</strong> The final percentage you want to see on your transcript (e.g., 90% for an A-, 80% for a B-).</li>
        <li><strong>Final Exam Weight:</strong> The percentage of your overall course grade that the final exam represents, as stated in your class syllabus (e.g., 20%, 30%).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>A Step-by-Step Example</h3>
      <p>Imagine you currently have an 82% in your chemistry class. You want to finish the semester with an 85% to maintain your scholarship. According to the syllabus, the final exam is worth 25% of your total grade. What do you need to score?</p>
      <ol>
        <li>First, convert the final weight to a decimal: <code>25% = 0.25</code>.</li>
        <li>Calculate the weight of everything else: <code>1 - 0.25 = 0.75</code>.</li>
        <li>Multiply your current grade by the non-final weight: <code>82 &times; 0.75 = 61.5</code>.</li>
        <li>Subtract that value from your target grade: <code>85 - 61.5 = 23.5</code>.</li>
        <li>Finally, divide by the final exam weight: <code>23.5 / 0.25 = 94%</code>.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>In this scenario, you would need to score exactly a 94% on the final exam to pull your overall grade up to an 85%.</p>

      <h3>What If the Score Is Over 100%?</h3>
      <p>If the calculator tells you that you need a score greater than 100%, it means that your target grade is mathematically impossible to achieve through the final exam alone unless your professor offers extra credit. In these situations, it is highly recommended to speak directly with your instructor to see if there are alternative ways to improve your grade, such as dropping the lowest quiz score or submitting an extra assignment.</p>

      <h3>Tips for Final Exam Prep</h3>
      <p>Knowing your target score is just the first step. Here are some proven strategies to help you hit that number:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Prioritize effectively:</strong> Use this calculator for all your classes. If you need a 98% in Biology but only a 40% in History to maintain your grades, spend the vast majority of your study time on Biology.</li>
        <li><strong>Review the syllabus:</strong> Professors often clearly state what topics the final will cover and whether it is cumulative. Don't waste time studying early semester material if the exam only covers the last month.</li>
        <li><strong>Form study groups:</strong> Explaining concepts to others is one of the most effective ways to solidify your own understanding and expose gaps in your knowledge.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>Why does the calculator say I need over 100%?</summary>
        <p>If the required score exceeds 100%, it means your current grade is too low, and the final exam does not carry enough weight to raise your overall grade to your target. Without extra credit, achieving your target grade is mathematically impossible.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What if I don't know my exact current grade?</summary>
        <p>If your professor hasn't updated the gradebook, you will need to estimate your current grade by calculating the weighted average of all your graded assignments so far. Alternatively, you can input a slightly lower, conservative estimate into the calculator to be safe.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I use this calculator if my class uses a point system instead of percentages?</summary>
        <p>Yes, but you must convert your points into percentages first. Divide your total earned points by the total possible points to find your current grade. Then, divide the points the final exam is worth by the total points in the entire course to find the final exam weight.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What does it mean if the calculator gives a negative number?</summary>
        <p>A negative required score means your current grade is so high, and your target grade is so low, that you could literally score a zero on the final exam and still achieve your target grade. Congratulations, you've already secured your grade!</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Does this calculator account for curved grading?</summary>
        <p>No. This calculator uses strict mathematical averages. It cannot account for bell curves, class-wide grade adjustments, or subjective professor grading. If your class is heavily curved, use this tool for a baseline, but know your actual required score might be lower.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const currentGradeInput = document.getElementById('current-grade');
      const targetGradeInput = document.getElementById('target-grade');
      const finalWeightInput = document.getElementById('final-weight');

      const errorMsg = document.getElementById('error-msg');
      const resultsDiv = document.getElementById('results');
      const resScore = document.getElementById('res-score');
      const resMessage = document.getElementById('res-message');

      function calculate() {
        errorMsg.style.display = 'none';

        const current = parseFloat(currentGradeInput.value);
        const target = parseFloat(targetGradeInput.value);
        const weight = parseFloat(finalWeightInput.value);

        if (isNaN(current) || isNaN(target) || isNaN(weight)) {
          resultsDiv.style.display = 'none';
          return;
        }

        if (weight <= 0 || weight >= 100) {
          errorMsg.textContent = 'Final Exam Weight must be between 0 and 100.';
          errorMsg.style.display = 'block';
          resultsDiv.style.display = 'none';
          return;
        }

        // Formula: Required = (Target - Current * (1 - Weight/100)) / (Weight / 100)
        const weightDecimal = weight / 100;
        const required = (target - (current * (1 - weightDecimal))) / weightDecimal;

        resScore.textContent = `${required.toFixed(2)}%`;
        resMessage.textContent = `on your final to get a ${target}% in the class.`;

        // Color coding
        if (required > 100) {
          resScore.style.color = '#ef4444'; // Red
          resMessage.innerHTML = `on your final to get a ${target}% in the class.<br><strong style="color: #ef4444; display: block; margin-top: 0.5rem;">Note: This score is over 100% and may be impossible without extra credit.</strong>`;
        } else if (required <= 0) {
          resScore.style.color = '#22c55e'; // Green
          resMessage.textContent = `on your final to get a ${target}% in the class. You've already secured this grade!`;
        } else {
          resScore.style.color = 'var(--accent-color)';
        }

        resultsDiv.style.display = 'block';
      }

      currentGradeInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);
      targetGradeInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);
      finalWeightInput.addEventListener('input', calculate);
    });
  </script>
  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .calculator-container { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .input-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .input-group { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .input-group label { display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); }
    input, select { background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px; width: 100%; font-size: 1rem; }
    input:focus, select:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 20%, transparent); }
    button { background: var(--accent-color); color: white; border: none; padding: 0.75rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; }
    button:hover { opacity: 0.9; }
    .result-card { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border: 1px solid var(--accent-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; text-align: center; }
    .result-value { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-color); }
    .error-message { color: #ef4444; background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 1rem; display: none; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    .explainer { margin-top: 3rem; }
    .explainer h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .explainer h3 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 2rem 0 1rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .explainer p { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer ul { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
